{"title_page": "Shingayi Kaondera", "text_new": "{{short description|Zimbabwean footballer}}\n{{EngvarB|date=May 2013}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=May 2013}}\n{{Infobox football biography\n| name = Shingayi Kaondera\n| image = \n| fullname = Shingayi Kaondera  \n| height = {{height|m=1.74}}\n| birth_date  = {{Birth date and age|df=yes|1982|7|31}}\n| birth_place = [[Seke District|Seke]], Zimbabwe\n| currentclub  = \n| clubnumber = \n| position = Midfielder\n| youthyears1 = \n| youthclubs1 = [[Darryn T]]\n| years1 = 1997  \n| years2 = 1997\u20131998  \n| years3 = 1998\u20131999 \n| years4 = 1999\u20132002 \n| years5 = 2002\u20132005  \n| years6 = 2005\u20132006  \n| years7 = 2006\u20132007  \n| years8 = 2007  \n| years9 = 2007\u20132008  \n| years10 = 2009\u20132010\n| years11 = 2010\u20132011\n| years12 = 2011\u20132012\n| clubs1 = Darryn T\n| clubs2 = [[Rak\u00f3w Cz\u0119stochowa]] \n| clubs3 = Darryn T\n| clubs4 = [[G\u00f3rnik Zabrze]]  \n| clubs5 = [[AEP Paphos]]  \n| clubs6 = [[Gaziantepspor]]  \n| clubs7 = [[Supersport United]]  \n| clubs8 = [[AEK Larnaca]]  \n| clubs9 = [[Nea Salamis Famagusta FC|Nea Salamina]]  \n| clubs10 = [[Digenis Morphou]]\n| clubs11= [[Chalkanoras Idaliou]]\n| clubs12= [[AEK Kouklia F.C.|AEK Kouklia]]\n| caps1 = 0   \n| caps2 = 0  \n| caps3 = 0  \n| caps4 = 52   \n| caps5 = 44  \n| caps6 = 6  \n| caps7 = 14  \n| caps8 = 10  \n| caps9 = 6  \n| caps10 = 21  \n| caps11 = 18  \n| goals1 = 0  \n| goals2 = 0  \n| goals3 = 0  \n| goals4 = 4  \n| goals5 = 6  \n| goals6 = 0  \n| goals7 = 3  \n| goals8 = 1  \n| goals9 = 0  \n| goals10 = 3 \n| goals11 = 4\n| nationalyears1 = 2002\u20132007\n| nationalteam1 = [[Zimbabwe national football team|Zimbabwe]]\n| nationalcaps1 = 18  \n| nationalgoals1 = 5 \n| pcupdate = 30 May 2010\n| ntupdate = 12 August 2007\n}}\n\n'''Shingayi Kaondera''' (born 31 July 1982 in [[Seke District|Seke]], [[Zimbabwe]]) is a [[association football|football]] [[midfielder]].\n\nKaondera started his career in [[Darryn T]] in 1997. Between 1999 and 2002 he played for the [[Poland|Polish]] clubs [[G\u00f3rnik Zabrze]] before signing for [[Cyprus|Cypriot]] [[Cypriot First Division]] outfit [[AEP Paphos]] during the 2005. In 2005\u20132006 he played for the [[Turkey|Turkish]] club [[Gaziantepspor]]. Next season he moved back in Africa and in [[Supersport United]] in South African [[Premier Soccer League]]. In July 2007 he signed a two-year contract with the Cypriot club [[AEK Larnaca]]. However, in January 2008 moved to [[Nea Salamis Famagusta FC|Nea Salamina]].\n\n==External links==\n* {{NFT player|pid=7403}}\n\n{{Zimbabwe Squad 2006 Africa Cup of Nations}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Kaondera, Shingayi}}\n[[Category:1982 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Zimbabwean footballers]]\n[[Category:Zimbabwe international footballers]]\n[[Category:2006 Africa Cup of Nations players]]\n[[Category:AEP Paphos FC players]]\n[[Category:Nea Salamis Famagusta FC players]]\n[[Category:AEK Larnaca FC players]]\n[[Category:Digenis Akritas Morphou FC players]]\n[[Category:Chalkanoras Idaliou players]]\n[[Category:AEK Kouklia F.C. players]]\n[[Category:G\u00f3rnik Zabrze players]]\n[[Category:Gaziantepspor footballers]]\n[[Category:Ekstraklasa players]]\n[[Category:S\u00fcper Lig players]]\n[[Category:Cypriot First Division players]]\n[[Category:Cypriot Second Division players]]\n[[Category:Zimbabwean expatriate footballers]]\n[[Category:Expatriate footballers in Turkey]]\n[[Category:Expatriate footballers in Cyprus]]\n[[Category:Expatriate footballers in Poland]]\n[[Category:Zimbabwean expatriate sportspeople in Poland]]\n[[Category:Association football midfielders]]\n\n\n{{Zimbabwe-footy-bio-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{EngvarB|date=May 2013}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=May 2013}}\n{{Infobox football biography\n| name = Shingayi Kaondera\n| image = \n| fullname = Shingayi Kaondera  \n| height = {{height|m=1.74}}\n| birth_date  = {{Birth date and age|df=yes|1982|7|31}}\n| birth_place = [[Seke District|Seke]], Zimbabwe