ades of America]]''\n* [[Anthony Bourdain]] \u2013 ''[[Anthony Bourdain: Parts Unknown]]'' (deceased)\n* [[Anderson Cooper]] \u2013 ''[[CNN Heroes]]''\n* [[Van Jones]] \u2013 ''The Messy Truth with Van Jones''<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.thedreamcorps.org/_the_messy_truth_hosted_by_van_jones_returns|title=\"The Messy Truth\" hosted by Van Jones returns to CNN|work=TheDreamCorps.org|date=2017|accessdate=4 April 2017}}</ref>\n* [[Mark Konkol]] \u2013 ''[[Chicagoland (TV series)|Chicagoland]]''\n* [[Lisa Ling]] \u2013 ''[[This Is Life with Lisa Ling]]''\n* [[Mike Rogers (Michigan politician)|Mike Rogers]] \u2013 ''[[Declassified (TV series)|Declassified: Untold Stories of American Spies]]''\n* [[Mike Rowe]] \u2013 ''[[Somebody's Gotta Do It]]''\n* [[Kevin Spacey]] \u2013 ''[[Race for the White House]]''\n* [[Morgan Spurlock]] \u2013 ''[[Morgan Spurlock Inside Man]]''\n* [[Meryl Streep]] \u2013 ''We Will Rise''\n* [[John Walsh (television host)|John Walsh]] \u2013 ''[[The Hunt with John Walsh]]''\n* [[Bill Weir]] \u2013 ''[[The Wonder List with Bill Weir]]''\n* [[Fareed Zakaria]] \u2013 ''The Most Powerful Man in the World''\n\n==Political and legal analysts==\n{{colbegin|colwidth=40em}}\n* [[Jim Acosta]] \u2014 Chief White House correspondent\n* [[Dana Bash]] \u2014 chief political correspondent\n* [[Richard Ben-Veniste]] \u2014 legal analyst\n* Rebecca Buck \u2014 political analyst\n* [[Carl Bernstein]] \u2014 political analyst\n* [[Wolf Blitzer]] \u2014 CNN lead political anchor\n* [[Gloria Borger]] \u2014 chief political analyst\n* [[David Chalian]] \u2014 senior political analyst; CNN political director\n* [[Harry Enten]] - political analyst and senior writer\n* [[Jamie Gangel]] \u2014 CNN special correspondent\n* [[David Gergen]] \u2014 senior political analyst\n* [[David Gregory (journalist)|David Gregory]] \u2014 political analyst\n* [[Maggie Haberman]] \u2014 political analyst\n* [[Joe Johns]] \u2014 senior Washington correspondent\n* [[Brianna Keilar]] \u20