{"title_page": "2017\u201318 Swiss Challenge League", "text_new": "{{update|date=June 2018}}\n{{Infobox football league season\n| competition                = [[Swiss Challenge League]]\n| season                     = 2017\u201318\n| logo                       = \n| pixels                     = 200\n| winners                    = [[Neuchatel Xamax]] \n| promoted                   = Neuchatel Xamax\n| relegated                  = [[FC Wohlen|Wohlen]]\n| league topscorer           = \n| biggest home win           = [[FC Schaffhausen|Schaffhausen]] 6\u20130 [[FC Rapperswil-Jona|Rapperswil-Jona]]<br /><small>(24 July 2017)\n| biggest away win           = [[FC Wohlen|Wohlen]] 1\u20134 [[FC Schaffhausen|Schaffhausen]]<br /><small>(31 July 2017)\n| highest scoring            = [[FC Schaffhausen|Schaffhausen]] 6\u20130 [[FC Rapperswil-Jona|Rapperswil-Jona]]<br /><small>(24 July 2017)\n| matches                    = 360\n| total goals                = 86\n| longest wins               = [[FC Schaffhausen|Schaffhausen]] (6 games)\n| longest unbeaten           = [[Neuch\u00e2tel Xamax]]  (21 games)\n| longest winless            = [[FC Aarau|Aarau]] (6 games)\n| longest losses             = [[FC Wohlen|Wohlen]] (4 games)\n| highest attendance         = \n| lowest attendance          = \n| attendance                 = \n| average attendance         = \n| prevseason                 = [[2016\u201317 Swiss Challenge League|2016\u201317]]\n| nextseason                 = [[2018\u201319 Swiss Challenge League|2018\u201319]]\n| updated                    = 21 July 2018\n}}\n\nThe '''2017\u201318 Swiss Challenge League''' (referred to as the '''Brack.ch Challenge League''' for sponsoring reasons) is the 15th season of the [[Swiss Challenge League]], the second tier of competitive football in Switzerland, under its current name. The season started on 21 July 2017 and is scheduled to end on 21 May 2018.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sfl.ch/fileadmin/user_upload/www.sfl.ch/downloads/spielplaene/Rahmenterminplan_SFL_2017-18_neu.pdf|title=Rahmenterminplan 2017/2018 - Calendrier 2017/2018|website=sfl.ch|accessdate=13 June 2017|language=German, French}}{{Dead link|date=September 2018 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref> The winter break began on 11 December 2017 and the league resumed on 2 February 2018.\n\n==Participating teams==\nA total of 10 teams participate in the league. [[2016\u201317 Swiss Challenge League]] champions [[FC Z\u00fcrich|Z\u00fcrich]] were promoted to the [[2017\u201318 Swiss Super League]]. They were replaced by [[FC Vaduz]], who got relegated after finishing last-placed in the [[2016\u201317 Swiss Super League]]. [[FC Le Mont|Le Mont]] was relegated after failing to renew their licence. They were replaced by [[FC Rapperswil-Jona|Rapperswil-Jona]], who won promotion from the 2016\u201317 [[Swiss Promotion League]].\n\n===Stadia and locations===\n{{Location map+|Switzerland|width=450|float=right\n |alt=Map of Switzerland with the locations of the Challenge League clubs\n |caption=Locations of clubs in the 2017\u201318 Challenge League\n |places=\n  {{Location map~|Switzerland|lat_deg=47|lat_min=24|lon_deg=08|lon_min=03|position=left|label=[[FC Aarau|Aarau]]}}\n  {{Location map~|Switzerland|lat_deg=45|lat_min=50|lon_deg=09|lon_min=02|position=|label=[[FC Chiasso|Chiasso]]}}\n  {{Location map~|Switzerland|lat_deg=47|lat_min=00|lon_deg=06|lon_min=56|position=right|label=[[Neuch\u00e2tel&nbsp;Xamax]]}}\n  {{Location map~|Switzerland|lat_deg=47|lat_min=14|lon_deg=08|lon_min=51|position=bottom|label=[[FC Rapperswil-Jona|Rapperswil-Jona]]}}\n  {{Location map~|Switzerland|lat_deg=47|lat_min=42|lon_deg=08|lon_min=38|position=left|label=[[FC Schaffhausen|Schaffhausen]]}}\n  {{Location map~|Switzerland|lat_deg=46|lat_min=10|lon_deg=06|lon_min=07|position=right|label=[[Servette FC|Servette]]}}\n  {{Location map~|Switzerland|lat_deg=47|lat_min=08|lon_deg=09|lon_min=30|position=bottom|label=[[FC Vaduz|Vaduz]]}}\n  {{Location map~|Switzerland|lat_deg=47|lat_min=28|lon_deg=09|lon_min=03|position=|label=[[FC Wil 1900|Wil]]}}\n  {{Location map~|Switzerland|lat_deg=47|lat_min=30|lon_deg=08|lon_min=45|position=left|label=[[FC Winterthur|Winterthur]]}}\n  {{Location map~|Switzerland|lat_deg=47|lat_min=21|lon_deg=08|lon_min=17|position=right|label=[[FC Wohlen|Wohlen]]}}\n}}\n\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! Team\n! Location\n! Stadium\n! Capacity\n|-\n| [[FC Aarau|Aarau]] || [[Aarau]] || [[Stadion Br\u00fcgglifeld]] || align=\"center\" | 8,000\n|- \n| [[FC Chiasso|Chiasso]] || [[Chiasso]] || [[Stadio Comunale (Chiasso)|Stadio Comunale Riva IV]] || align=\"center\" | 5,000\n|-\n| [[Neuch\u00e2tel Xamax]] || [[Neuch\u00e2tel]] || [[Stade de la Maladi\u00e8re]] || align=\"center\" | 12,000\n|-\n| [[FC Rapperswil-Jona|Rapperswil-Jona]] || [[Rapperswil-Jona]] || [[Stadion Gr\u00fcnfeld]] || align=\"center\" | 2,500 \n|-\n| [[Servette FC|Servette]] || [[Geneva]] || [[Stade de Gen\u00e8ve]] || align=\"center\" | 30,084\n|- \n| [[FC Schaffhausen|Schaffhausen]] || [[Schaffhausen]] || [[Stadion Breite]]<br />[[LIPO Park Schaffhausen]] || align=\"center\" | 4,200<br />8,200\n|-\n| [[FC Vaduz|Vaduz]] || {{flagicon|Liechtenstein}} [[Vaduz]] || [[Rheinpark Stadion]] || align=\"center\" | 7,584\n|- \n| [[FC Wil 1900|Wil]] || [[Wil]] || [[Stadion Bergholz|IGP Arena]] || align=\"center\" | 6,958\n|-\n| [[FC Winterthur|Winterthur]] || [[Winterthur]] || [[Sch\u00fctzenwiese]] || align=\"center\" | 8,550\n|-\n| [[FC Wohlen|Wohlen]] || [[Wohlen, Aargau|Wohlen]] || [[Stadion Niedermatten]] || align=\"center\" | 3,624 \n|}\n\n===Personnel===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! Team\n! Manager\n|- \n| [[FC Aarau|Aarau]] || {{flagicon|SUI}} [[Stephan Keller]] (caretaker)\n|- \n| [[FC Chiasso|Chiasso]] || {{flagicon|ITA}} Baldassarre Raineri\n|-\n| [[Neuch\u00e2tel Xamax]] || {{flagicon|SUI}} [[Michel Decastel]]\n|- \n| [[FC Rapperswil-Jona|Rapperswil-Jona]] || {{flagicon|SUI}} [[Urs Meier (footballer)|Urs Meier]]